                        </div>
                    

                    

                    



                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>« <a href="/news-07-2018">July 2018</a> | <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="/news-08-2018">August 2018</a></span> | <a href="/news-09-2018">September 2018</a> »</strong></p>
</div>
<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p>We're doing a bunch of new things for this month's Site News! Changes include a revamped Fan-content area, a contest recap, and an editor's choice section! Feedback on all of these things would be greatly appreciated, so please let us know in the comments what you think about it.</p>
<p>Before we start though, I just want to give a huge thank you to TSATPWTCOTTTADC and Uncle Nicolini, without whom none of this would have been possible. Seriously, they're amazing.</p>
<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-oct-hub">SCP OCT Hub</a> - In the void left by March Madness, a new unofficial site arena has opened up. Original Characters vs Original Characters, the ultimate showdown of ultimate destiny and Posting has begun. Organized by PeppersGhost.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-series-5">SCP Series 5</a> - The 4000 contest has finally concluded (check out the post-game stats page below) and Series 5 is finally open to contributions! Get out there and start making articles!</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Event Featured Articles</span></h4>
<p>This month had no theme! Instead, winners from the previous <a href="/doomsday-contest">Doomsday Contest</a> got their articles featured! Check them out below!</p>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>The featured articles for August were <a href="/scp-3379">SCP-3379</a> (&quot;D-11424 and the Arctic Meat Hole of Infinite Wonders&quot;) by Darkstuff and Weryllium, <a href="/scp-3564">SCP-3564</a> (&quot;The Immortal Bard, Act Ⅱ: Return of Shakespeare&quot;) by MaliceAforethought, <a href="/scp-3934">SCP-3934</a> (&quot;For Sale: Loch Ness Monsters&quot;) by Modern_erasmus, and <a href="/parts">Parts</a> by Fieldstone.
<ul>
<li>In <a href="/scp-3379">SCP-3379</a>, D-11424, inter-dimensional free-man, is put through a series of challenges, possibly for the right to his kidneys. I'm not sure though, don't speak walrus.</li>
<li>In <a href="/scp-3564">SCP-3564</a>, Shakespeare comes back from the dead to do&#8230;something. Certainly something.</li>
<li>In <a href="/scp-3934">SCP-3934</a>, MC&amp;D play fetch with the Foundation using the Loch Ness Monster.</li>
<li>In <a href="/parts">Parts</a>, sacrifice is made apparent in the face of overwhelming good.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Editor's Choice Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3009">SCP-3009</a> (&quot;Hi, I'm Your Snappelganger!&quot;) by Keyii - Wonderful characterization of lovable characters will have you attached to Stacey Lee quickly.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3758">SCP-3758</a> (&quot;The Last Dodo&quot;) by daveyoufool - A very predictable article until it very much isn't.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3844">SCP-3844</a> (&quot;To Slay a Dragon&quot;) by Captain Kirby - Science cannot truly kill whimsy.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4028">SCP-4028</a> (&quot;La Historia de Don Quixote de la Mancha&quot;) by The Great Hippo - Huge bias here, but I love Don Quixote and this meta-narrative is truly incredible.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4239">SCP-4239</a> (&quot;Project Kenowhere Central Volunteer Hub&#8230;&quot;) by scarhaver and Dolphinslugchugger - Pretty much a GAW 001 proposal.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-4113">SCP-4113</a> (&quot;Long is the Way You Must Wander&quot;) by Doctor Cimmerian - Rule of cool reigns supreme here. Vikings, space, and lightsabers.</li>
<li><a href="/inside-the-wall">Inside the Wall</a> by Taylor Itkin - This is truly inspired and I highly suggest it.</li>
<li><a href="/intermission">Intermission</a> by tygently - I had no idea what Third Law was prior to this, but the article got me interested in exploring the canon.</li>
<li><a href="/listpages-magic-and-you">ListPages Magic and You</a> by Croquembouche - The most helpful tool once could imagine for learning Listpages wizardy.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h4><span>SCP-4000 Contest</span></h4>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Click&nbsp;here&nbsp;to&nbsp;show&nbsp;the&nbsp;recap!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/scp4000contesthub/Zhange4000labelled.jpg" alt="Zhange4000labelled.jpg" class="image" />
<p style="text-align: center;">Banner by zhange</p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:250%;"><strong>SCP-4000 Contest: Site News Edition!</strong></span></p>
<p><br />
The SCP-4000 contest was a blast! There were lots of really unique and interesting articles with cool twists on not just world history, but site and in-universe history. As good as many of them were, there could only be one SCP-4000. Folks, I present to you your winner!</p>
<hr />
<div style="background-color: #fffff0; font-size: 150%; border: solid 1px #cc0000; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center; width: 400px; margin: 0 auto;">
<p>Congratulations to<br />
PeppersGhost<br />
For winning the SCP-4000 Contest!<br />
With: <a href="/scp-4000">Taboo</a></p>
</div>
<p><strong><span style="color: green">Taboo</span></strong> is a dark, twisted expansion on <a href="/scp-001-o5">that time the Foundation committed genocide.</a> <strong><span style="color: green">The contest winner</span></strong> has caused quite a stir within the community, with many people talking about it! Here are some notable creations!</p>
<ul>
<li>Do you have questions about SCP-4000? Well, look no further than <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/SCPDeclassified/comments/920z3u/scp4000_taboo_contest_entry/">r/SCPDeclassified on SCP-4000</a> and Doctor Cimmerian's <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=65ZOteo-Pvo">Object Class Explained: SCP-4000.</a></li>
<li>Speaking of Doctor Cimmerian, he also narrated the article. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lyFuSYbLtLc">Check it out!</a></li>
<li>pastarasta1 made an SCP-4000-inspired animation. <a href="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/pastarasta1-s-simply-epic-artpage/taboo2">Here it is!</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4000-j">SCP-4000-J</a>, or '2boo' by djkaktus is a funnier take on SCP-4000!</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://www.scp-wiki.net/local--files/news-08-2018/PeppersGhostTaboo.jpg" alt="PeppersGhostTaboo.jpg" class="image" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">'Taboo' by PeppersGhost!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>&quot;It's like a British public safety poster crossed with an Art Deco fever dream.&quot;</em> — Taffeta</p>
<hr />
<div style="background-color: #fffff0; font-size: 150%; border: solid 1px #cc0000; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center; width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
<p>But what's a contest without other competitors?<br />
Let's meet the other top contenders!<br />
2nd: djkaktus with: <a href="/scp-4444">Bush V. Gore</a><br />
3rd (tie): CadaverCommander with <a href="/scp-4999">Someone To Watch Over Us</a><br />
3rd (tie): DrClef with <a href="/scp-4960">Kedesh-Nanaya, Or: Why The Foundation Published Hentai to Awaken a Mesopotamian Love Goddess</a><br />
4th: IHP with <a href="/scp-4100">Future Imperfect</a><br />
5th: Mathbrush with <a href="/scp-4500">Socratic Containment Procedures</a></p>
</div>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:250%;"><strong>Fun contest facts!</strong></span></p>
<p><br />
Here is a compilation of interesting facts on the contest, compiled by scpcrnp. Click <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-6744346/post-4k-contest-supplemental-awards-polls-and-misc-data">here</a> for more!</p>
<ul>
<li>ihp posted the first entry (<em>&quot;Future Imperfect&quot;</em>) at 30 Jun 2018, 22:59.</li>
<li>Peppersghost's <em>&quot;Taboo&quot;</em> received 100+ consecutive upvotes before receiving a downvote.</li>
<li>PeppersGhost led for all but 47 hrs 35 min of the contest. The remainder was held by Ihp (<em>&quot;Future Imperfect&quot;</em>).</li>
<li>14 members posted their first works as a successful 4Kon entry:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p>GentleGifts - <em>&quot;Alexandria Eternal&quot;</em><br />
Researcher Blasko - <em>&quot;Save Her&quot;</em><br />
higans - <em>&quot;The Keepers&quot;</em><br />
Adriatica - <em>&quot;The Day The Music Died&quot;</em><br />
EbenezerShark - <em>&quot;The Last Question&quot;</em><br />
MacWarren - <em>&quot;We Die In The Dark&quot;</em><br />
LuluTheRadiant - <em>&quot;The World's Greatest Teacher Is History&quot;</em><br />
incidental_cabbage - <em>&quot;History Is Written By The Victors&quot;</em><br />
DoctorNovakaine - <em>&quot;Retrochronal Observation Tank&quot;</em><br />
Logarithmika- <em>&quot;Saving Archimedes&quot;</em><br />
ArmLengthRadius - <em>&quot;We Have Assumed Control&quot;</em><br />
Uncannyon - <em>&quot;It Won't Stop Screaming&quot;</em><br />
Papa Sen - <em>&quot;On Cowboys, Catholicism, and the Cretaceous&quot;</em><br />
Filayoung - <em>&quot;Twenty Text Messages&quot;</em></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Modern_Erasmus and tretter's 4K entry, <em>&quot;The Black Moon Howls From Beyond The Edge Of Time,&quot;</em> was the final one posted, at 12AM on August 1st with 18 seconds left in the contest.
<ul>
<li>Additionally, it was the latest entrant to amass 100+ votes!</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><em>&quot;Than Teach Ten Thousand Stars how Not to Dance&quot;</em> by LordStonefish featured the most footnotes of any entry (28). Each of these is the same statement.</li>
<li>Peppersghost made a version of <em>&quot;Taboo&quot;</em> for the colorblind.</li>
<li>There were 3 new object classes introduced in the contest:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p>djkaktus - &quot;Ticonderoga&quot; - <em>&quot;Bush v. Gore&quot;</em><br />
higans - &quot;Eparch&quot; - <em>&quot;The Keepers&quot;</em><br />
EbenezerShark - &quot;Gödel&quot; - <em>&quot;The Last Last Question&quot;</em></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li><em>&quot;A Dream Come True&quot;</em> by Communism will win and kinchtheknifeblade was the most discussed article in the contest with 190 comments.</li>
<li><em>&quot;Kagemusha&quot;</em> by weizhong received the best average score with a 95.8% positive rating.</li>
<li><em>&quot;Bush v. Gore&quot;</em> by djkaktus received the most net votes with a total of 525.</li>
<li>5 contest entries were co-written, including:</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p>Modern_Erasmus and tretter - <em>&quot;The Black Moon Howls From Beyond The Edge Of Time&quot;</em><br />
Uncle Nicolini, SecretCrow, and Papa Sen - <em>&quot;On Cowboys, Catholicism, and the Cretaceous&quot;</em><br />
Communism will win and kinchtheknifeblade - <em>&quot;A Dream Come True&quot;</em><br />
A Random Day and The Great Hippo - <em>&quot;Dark Side of the Moon&quot;</em><br />
ArmLengthRadius and Gibberingeloquence - <em>&quot;We Have Assumed Control&quot;</em></p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:250%;"><strong>Editor's Picks!</strong></span></p>
<p><br />
Varaxous</p>
<blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-4069">SCP-4069: Out of Range</a> by Cyantreuse is a pretty excellent read. Don't let the beginning fool you, this isn't a failed self-deletion. There's a lot going here, much of it deeper than it may seem. 100% worth a second read through, 200% worth reading through the follow up.<br />
<a href="/scp-4999">SCP-4999: Someone to Watch Over us</a> by CadaverCommander. All I need to say about this one is that it's been a long time since I've read something and gotten chills because of it.<br />
<a href="/scp-4017">SCP-4017: An Epilogue, Too Late to Matter</a> by 9Volt. There's a LOT of stuff here and all of it is extremely interesting. Exploring some aspects of Volt's own Second Hytoth, this piece really takes the 'History' theme to the max, exploring a lot of the Foundationverse through out. Warning: reading it may cause you to spend hours reading the other Church of the Second Hytoth articles.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Uncle Nicolini</p>
<blockquote>
<p><a href="/scp-4007">SCP-4007: Kagemusha</a> by weizhong is by far my favorite article in the entire contest. It's expertly written and does everything to make you say 'Wait, what?' before the big reveal. I won't spoil it for you, so I highly encourage you to give it a read.<br />
A few other favorites of mine (in no particular order) are as follows;<br />
<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4444">SCP-4444: Bush v. Gore</a> by djkaktus<br />
<a href="/scp-4041">SCP-4041: Teach the Controversy</a> by Weryllium<br />
<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4999">SCP-4999: Someone to Watch Over Us</a> by CadaverCommander<br />
<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4004">SCP-4004: A Dream Come True</a> by Communism will win and kinchtheknifeblade<br />
<a href="/scp-4300">SCP-4300: To Lose One's Soul</a> by Bluedanoob.<br />
<a href="/scp-4890">SCP-4890: Dr. Wondertainment's Guide to History</a> by Baronjoe</p>
</blockquote>
